1
00:00:10,135 --> 00:00:17,142
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:01:05,732 --> 00:01:08,193
Secretary Kim gave that
to Cyrus.

3
00:01:08,276 --> 00:01:11,613
I think he's starting to fall
in love with Secretary Kim.

4
00:01:11,696 --> 00:01:14,699
Why did you choose this setting
for your book?

5
00:01:14,783 --> 00:01:16,618
This place has witnessed
so many things.

6
00:01:16,701 --> 00:01:17,827
It's not perfect anymore.

7
00:01:17,911 --> 00:01:20,830
I think there's no such thing
as perfect.

8
00:01:20,914 --> 00:01:22,207
Not even the boss.

9
00:01:22,290 --> 00:01:23,875
Sometimes, I wish I was perfect.

10
00:01:23,958 --> 00:01:26,002
That way, I wouldn't
hurt my family

11
00:01:26,085 --> 00:01:27,670
or anybody else,
for that matter.

12
00:01:27,754 --> 00:01:29,923
You should stop playing
with Secretary Kim's feelings.

13
00:01:30,006 --> 00:01:31,466
Why do you assume
I'm playing around?

14
00:01:31,549 --> 00:01:33,802
I like her.
I'm willing to negotiate.

15
00:01:33,885 --> 00:01:36,805
If I give up Secretary Kim,
would you forgive me?

16
00:01:36,888 --> 00:01:37,847
No.

17
00:01:37,931 --> 00:01:40,391
I think my anxiety's
getting worse lately,

18
00:01:40,475 --> 00:01:42,477
especially when I'm
with Sec. Kim.

19
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:43,895
That's because
you're holding back.

20
00:01:43,978 --> 00:01:45,688
You need to stop lying to her.

21
00:01:45,772 --> 00:01:49,359
The truth will release you
from your anxiety.

22
00:01:50,819 --> 00:01:57,826
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

23
00:01:59,244 --> 00:02:02,163
Donny, it wasn't your fault.

24
00:02:03,957 --> 00:02:05,959
Well, it's not just that, Doc.

25
00:02:06,876 --> 00:02:08,086
In my head,

26
00:02:08,169 --> 00:02:11,339
I know what happened
to Sec. Kim wasn't my fault.

27
00:02:13,007 --> 00:02:14,384
And also,

28
00:02:14,467 --> 00:02:18,763
she hasn't blamed Ninja Boy
even once for what happened.

29
00:02:20,348 --> 00:02:21,850
Then, what is it?

30
00:02:23,852 --> 00:02:25,436
[BRANDON] Sec. Kim!

31
00:02:27,146 --> 00:02:28,481
- [GASPS]
- [KIM SCREAMS]

32
00:02:28,565 --> 00:02:31,568
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

33
00:02:31,651 --> 00:02:32,944
[GASPS]

34
00:02:35,822 --> 00:02:37,991
Doc, what if
I tell her the truth

35
00:02:38,074 --> 00:02:40,785
and she starts
remembering things?

36
00:02:40,869 --> 00:02:42,871
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

37
00:02:42,954 --> 00:02:44,831
I don't want her to be like me.

38
00:02:44,914 --> 00:02:47,375
[SCOFFS] So, what?

39
00:02:48,626 --> 00:02:50,753
What is so wrong about you?

40
00:02:52,714 --> 00:02:55,174
Doc, I'm not perfect.

41
00:02:56,926 --> 00:02:59,721
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

42
00:02:59,804 --> 00:03:01,848
I'm constantly haunted
by my trauma.

43
00:03:01,931 --> 00:03:04,767
I'm on meds 24/7.

44
00:03:04,851 --> 00:03:07,729
I can't form any proper
relationship with anyone.

45
00:03:07,812 --> 00:03:08,938
I'm...

46
00:03:09,647 --> 00:03:12,108
I can't even kiss
the girl I like.

47
00:03:12,609 --> 00:03:13,776
Doc...

48
00:03:14,736 --> 00:03:16,321
I'm a mess.

49
00:03:16,404 --> 00:03:17,989
[SIGHS]

50
00:03:18,072 --> 00:03:21,242
Brandon, you are not a mess.

51
00:03:21,326 --> 00:03:23,703
You are suffering from PTSD.

52
00:03:24,287 --> 00:03:25,830
That's an illness.

53
00:03:25,914 --> 00:03:27,498
And it's not you.

54
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:31,878
I just don't want her
to live a life like this.

55
00:03:34,505 --> 00:03:35,882
Like mine.

56
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:39,969
Is that really the case,
Brandon?

57
00:03:41,137 --> 00:03:43,222
Or are you just really afraid...

58
00:03:44,223 --> 00:03:45,725
...of rejection?

59
00:03:49,979 --> 00:03:53,733
Look, no one knows
how Kim will react

60
00:03:53,816 --> 00:03:55,568
if she finds out the truth.

61
00:03:56,611 --> 00:03:59,364
Everyone reacts differently.

62
00:04:00,031 --> 00:04:06,913
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

63
00:04:08,748 --> 00:04:10,291
I'm not going to risk it.

64
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:23,054
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

65
00:04:23,137 --> 00:04:26,057
[KIM] You're not a
stranger to me, Sir Cyrus.

66
00:04:26,140 --> 00:04:28,309
You also helped me out before.

67
00:04:28,393 --> 00:04:33,898
So if I can help you
with anything, I will.

68
00:04:33,982 --> 00:04:36,234
You should've said
something sooner, Brandon.

69
00:04:36,317 --> 00:04:39,237
Well, it's too late now.
I have feelings for her.

70
00:04:42,657 --> 00:04:44,617
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

71
00:04:47,495 --> 00:04:48,579
Hey, dear.

72
00:04:51,374 --> 00:04:53,918
- Is everything okay?
- [SIGHS]

73
00:04:54,002 --> 00:04:56,587
I deserve to be happy, too,
right, Ma?

74
00:04:58,047 --> 00:04:59,924
Of course.

75
00:05:00,008 --> 00:05:04,679
You deserve anything
your heart and mind desire.

76
00:05:06,514 --> 00:05:07,807
But for now,

77
00:05:07,890 --> 00:05:10,935
let's get going before
your dad's temper flares up.

78
00:05:11,019 --> 00:05:12,353
- [CHUCKLES]
- Let's go.

79
00:05:12,437 --> 00:05:14,188
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

80
00:05:15,565 --> 00:05:17,859
Yes, Sir Walt, I've brought
the other collaterals.

81
00:05:17,942 --> 00:05:20,111
I'm just waiting
for Steph and Jordy.

82
00:05:20,778 --> 00:05:22,238
Thank you.

83
00:05:22,322 --> 00:05:25,491
Yes, Sir Walt. I got this.
Thank you.

84
00:05:28,327 --> 00:05:29,662
Okay...

85
00:05:29,746 --> 00:05:32,540
- Hey, wait up! Wait, wait!
- [QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

86
00:05:33,374 --> 00:05:36,586
Sorry. Sir Philip asked me
to run an errand first.

87
00:05:36,669 --> 00:05:38,212
OMG, girl!

88
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:40,214
You're on fire!

89
00:05:40,298 --> 00:05:43,259
- Oh my god!
- Small things!

90
00:05:43,342 --> 00:05:45,094
You know we're gorgeous 24/7,

91
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:47,847
but I glammed up a bit more
today for the event.

92
00:05:47,930 --> 00:05:50,308
Oh, for the event
or for someone else?

93
00:05:50,391 --> 00:05:52,143
Who are you dressing up for?

94
00:05:52,226 --> 00:05:53,811
What do you mean, who?

95
00:05:53,895 --> 00:05:55,688
[MOCKING]
"What do you mean, who?"

96
00:05:55,772 --> 00:05:58,441
- Whatever! Stop it!
- Oh my god!

97
00:05:58,983 --> 00:06:00,485
Can we hitch a ride, too?

98
00:06:00,568 --> 00:06:02,403
Sure. "We"?

99
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:07,408
Oh, me and Maya from Marketing.

100
00:06:07,492 --> 00:06:09,660
- [STEPH] Hmm...
- Is there still space?

101
00:06:09,744 --> 00:06:12,121
- Hm? Yeah, I think so.
- [PHONE CHIMES]

102
00:06:13,081 --> 00:06:15,208
Um, Jordy, I need your help.

103
00:06:15,291 --> 00:06:19,378
Miss Jane forgot something.
I have to go up and get it.

104
00:06:19,462 --> 00:06:21,214
Okay, I'll go with you.

105
00:06:21,589 --> 00:06:23,424
Um, wait for us, okay?

106
00:06:23,508 --> 00:06:24,634
Come on.

107
00:06:27,553 --> 00:06:29,138
Get in, Kim Marie!

108
00:06:29,639 --> 00:06:31,933
Sir Walt is waiting,
so hurry up!

109
00:06:32,391 --> 00:06:34,143
What about Jordy and Maya?

110
00:06:34,227 --> 00:06:37,063
They can catch up later.
There's a second trip, anyway.

111
00:06:37,146 --> 00:06:38,439
Now, let's go!

112
00:06:40,108 --> 00:06:46,405
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

113
00:06:46,489 --> 00:06:48,491
[KIM] Sir Walt, where are we
on the preparations?

114
00:06:48,574 --> 00:06:50,451
Have you briefed Iñigo?

115
00:06:50,535 --> 00:06:53,371
Well, I assigned Sarah
to handle the host,

116
00:06:53,454 --> 00:06:55,081
but she's not here yet.

117
00:06:55,164 --> 00:06:58,209
Just assign it to Miss Jane.
She can handle it.

118
00:06:58,292 --> 00:07:00,169
Miss Sarah told me
over the phone

119
00:07:00,253 --> 00:07:02,213
that she's suffering
from rashes today.

120
00:07:02,296 --> 00:07:03,631
You mean, an allergy?

121
00:07:03,714 --> 00:07:05,550
She should watch
what she's eating.

122
00:07:05,633 --> 00:07:07,885
I told her
to get herself checked

123
00:07:07,969 --> 00:07:09,720
so she'll know what caused it

124
00:07:09,804 --> 00:07:12,140
and we can be aware of it, too.

125
00:07:13,099 --> 00:07:15,643
So, we're one man down.
What will happen now?

126
00:07:15,726 --> 00:07:18,771
Don't worry.
We're Team Bida Best.

127
00:07:18,855 --> 00:07:20,106
We can do this.

128
00:07:20,690 --> 00:07:22,942
Okay, um... Kim Marie,

129
00:07:23,025 --> 00:07:25,486
inform me right away
once the host arrives.

130
00:07:25,570 --> 00:07:29,031
And work on the interview
questions with Miss Jane,

131
00:07:29,115 --> 00:07:32,285
because Miss Carlota is strict
about the questions

132
00:07:32,368 --> 00:07:34,829
that can be asked
to Sir Cyrus, okay?

133
00:07:34,912 --> 00:07:37,081
I thought I was assigned
to Morpheus?

134
00:07:37,165 --> 00:07:39,500
Miss Carlota has requested
for Sec. Kim

135
00:07:39,584 --> 00:07:41,377
to be assigned to Sir Cyrus.

136
00:07:41,460 --> 00:07:44,005
When will the boss arrive?

137
00:07:44,088 --> 00:07:47,425
I called Baldo, and he said
they're on their way here.

138
00:07:47,508 --> 00:07:49,051
- Okay.
- Steph,

139
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:53,681
make sure Sir Philip's ready
to welcome the VIPs, okay?

140
00:07:53,764 --> 00:07:55,308
- And...
- [QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

141
00:07:55,391 --> 00:07:56,684
Steph?

142
00:07:57,351 --> 00:07:58,477
[KIM] Steph?

143
00:07:59,187 --> 00:08:00,229
Steph! [SNAPS FINGERS]

144
00:08:00,313 --> 00:08:02,273
- Steph, focus!
- Huh?!

145
00:08:02,356 --> 00:08:05,860
Uh, yes. Noted.

146
00:08:05,943 --> 00:08:07,361
- Whatever.
- [PHONE VIBRATING]

147
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:09,280
Hold on.

148
00:08:09,822 --> 00:08:10,907
Yes?

149
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:13,284
Uh, I think they're here.

150
00:08:13,367 --> 00:08:15,328
- The boss?
- No.

151
00:08:15,411 --> 00:08:18,039
Sir Cyrus,
and he's looking for you.

152
00:08:19,207 --> 00:08:21,542
Alright,
I'll leave you guys to it.

153
00:08:21,626 --> 00:08:24,212
- Sir Walt, take over.
- Right, got it.

154
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:26,839
Um... guys, listen up.

155
00:08:26,923 --> 00:08:29,884
We have 20 minutes
'til showtime.

156
00:08:29,967 --> 00:08:32,720
- [JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING]
- Alright. Bye.

157
00:08:33,596 --> 00:08:36,849
Oh. This looks like
another successful event.

158
00:08:36,933 --> 00:08:39,977
Don't congratulate me.
My son did all the work.

159
00:08:40,061 --> 00:08:42,647
- [LAUGHS]
- Sandro, you remember our son?

160
00:08:42,730 --> 00:08:45,566
Brandon, am I right? Your father
can't stop talking about you.

161
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:48,903
No, my friend,
this is my eldest son,

162
00:08:48,986 --> 00:08:51,113
the one who followed his dreams.

163
00:08:52,114 --> 00:08:53,449
And succeeded.

164
00:08:55,826 --> 00:08:57,203
Cyrus, sir.

165
00:08:57,286 --> 00:08:58,287
Nice to meet you.

166
00:08:58,371 --> 00:09:02,541
Oh, but his fans
simply call him "Morpheus."

167
00:09:03,042 --> 00:09:05,253
- As in the bestselling author?
- Yes.

168
00:09:05,336 --> 00:09:08,297
Then it's an honor to meet you.
My daughter is a big fan.

169
00:09:08,381 --> 00:09:10,383
- Oh!
- Pleasure's all mine, sir.

170
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:14,095
- I'll see you later, okay?
- Yeah.

171
00:09:14,178 --> 00:09:15,471
- Enjoy yourself.
- Alright.

172
00:09:15,554 --> 00:09:16,889
There's champagne
and canapes there, okay?

173
00:09:16,973 --> 00:09:18,099
See you.

174
00:09:19,308 --> 00:09:20,726
Oh, the Parks are here.

175
00:09:21,936 --> 00:09:24,313
Robert. Long time, no see again.

176
00:09:24,397 --> 00:09:26,524
Nice to see you,
Mr. Park, Mrs. Park.

177
00:09:26,607 --> 00:09:28,359
- Hi.
- Welcome to the event.

178
00:09:28,442 --> 00:09:30,903
You know my wife, Carlota,
and my son Cyrus.

179
00:09:30,987 --> 00:09:32,947
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

180
00:09:33,030 --> 00:09:34,657
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you, too.

181
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:35,825
- Well...
- Shall we?

182
00:09:35,908 --> 00:09:37,660
- Yes. Yes.
- Shall we?

183
00:09:42,581 --> 00:09:46,002
I love it, Sir Cyrus.
It's such a light read.

184
00:09:46,085 --> 00:09:49,630
Very heartfelt, tender,
and very honest.

185
00:09:55,845 --> 00:09:57,179
You're too kind.

186
00:09:57,888 --> 00:09:59,598
It's just my opinion.

187
00:09:59,682 --> 00:10:02,226
I'm sure it will be
another bestseller.

188
00:10:05,021 --> 00:10:09,275
It's the first time
they'll see my face as Morpheus.

189
00:10:10,443 --> 00:10:14,155
If you feel nervous,
just look to stage right.

190
00:10:14,238 --> 00:10:16,365
I'll be there to cheer you on.

191
00:10:17,074 --> 00:10:18,701
Well, good luck later.

192
00:10:19,035 --> 00:10:20,328
Wait. Um...

193
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:24,540
I was hoping
I could talk to you. I...

194
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:27,835
There's something
I want to tell you.

195
00:10:27,918 --> 00:10:32,423
[SULLEN MUSIC PLAYING]

196
00:10:34,675 --> 00:10:35,760
Donny.

197
00:10:42,683 --> 00:10:44,310
Um, boss...

198
00:10:45,478 --> 00:10:48,230
You've arrived, boss. Um...

199
00:10:48,314 --> 00:10:52,234
Sir Cyrus just asked me
to review his speech.

200
00:10:55,905 --> 00:10:58,574
Well, if he has to do that,
then maybe...

201
00:10:58,657 --> 00:11:01,327
...he's not as good a writer
as he claims to be.

202
00:11:04,705 --> 00:11:06,248
- Boss...
- [WALTER] Sec. Kim.

203
00:11:06,332 --> 00:11:09,919
Sec. Kim, Sir Cyrus,
the program's about to start.

204
00:11:10,002 --> 00:11:12,838
Let's be on standby over here.

205
00:11:20,679 --> 00:11:24,392
"In the tempestuous sea of life,
she became my anchor.

206
00:11:25,309 --> 00:11:28,020
Once adrift in the dark currents
of despair,

207
00:11:28,521 --> 00:11:30,689
she arrived
as a glimmer of hope."

208
00:11:30,773 --> 00:11:35,361
[TENDER MUSIC PLAYING]

209
00:11:36,779 --> 00:11:39,573
He's so giving, Miss Kim!

210
00:11:39,657 --> 00:11:41,992
He looks so inspired.

211
00:11:43,035 --> 00:11:46,288
You're quite the fangirl.
You've even noticed that.

212
00:11:46,872 --> 00:11:49,458
Just listen to him closely.

213
00:11:49,542 --> 00:11:52,002
He's literally talking
about a girl.

214
00:11:53,129 --> 00:11:56,841
Whoever she is,
she's the luckiest.

215
00:11:58,884 --> 00:12:02,805
"Her eyes held the serenity
that calmed the storm within me.

216
00:12:02,888 --> 00:12:04,849
She saved me from drowning.

217
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:11,230
With her, I found not just
my inspiration,

218
00:12:11,772 --> 00:12:13,399
but a reason to live.

219
00:12:14,108 --> 00:12:17,611
In her, I discovered a love
that redeems.

220
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:20,197
And in her embrace,

221
00:12:20,781 --> 00:12:24,493
I vowed never to be lost again."

222
00:12:27,997 --> 00:12:33,419
[APPLAUSE]

223
00:12:39,675 --> 00:12:42,720
Very moving, indeed.
Very moving.

224
00:12:43,220 --> 00:12:46,432
It's my honor to finally
meet you in person.

225
00:12:46,515 --> 00:12:48,392
[CHUCKLES] Speaking of personal,

226
00:12:48,476 --> 00:12:51,562
you mentioned before
that everything you write

227
00:12:51,645 --> 00:12:54,982
is based on your own
personal experiences, right?

228
00:12:55,065 --> 00:12:56,692
Well, most of them.

229
00:12:56,775 --> 00:12:58,027
- Yes.
- Well, earlier,

230
00:12:58,110 --> 00:13:00,488
you were talking about a girl.

231
00:13:01,113 --> 00:13:04,158
Um... so tell me, is she real?

232
00:13:04,783 --> 00:13:08,454
I mean, you described her
so vividly.

233
00:13:09,163 --> 00:13:11,081
A girlfriend, perhaps?

234
00:13:11,165 --> 00:13:17,922
[TENDER MUSIC CONTINUES]

235
00:13:18,005 --> 00:13:19,256
No. Uh...

236
00:13:20,758 --> 00:13:21,759
Not...

237
00:13:22,218 --> 00:13:23,969
[CHUCKLES SHEEPISHLY]
Not yet.

238
00:13:25,346 --> 00:13:27,264
But she's very special to me.

239
00:13:27,348 --> 00:13:28,766
[IÑIGO] Oh...

240
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:32,561
Is this the girl you were with
when you were kidnapped?

241
00:13:32,645 --> 00:13:37,733
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

242
00:13:44,281 --> 00:13:45,699
Excuse me?

243
00:13:45,783 --> 00:13:49,703
I was told you went missing
for a couple of days

244
00:13:49,787 --> 00:13:51,497
when you were young.

245
00:13:51,580 --> 00:13:53,499
Was she that girl
with you at that time?

246
00:13:53,582 --> 00:14:00,130
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

247
00:14:06,512 --> 00:14:07,930
[CHUCKLES]

248
00:14:10,099 --> 00:14:12,643
Where did that question
come from?

249
00:14:13,561 --> 00:14:15,229
These are just questions

250
00:14:15,312 --> 00:14:17,982
that your longtime fans
want answered.

251
00:14:18,065 --> 00:14:19,191
Am I right?

252
00:14:19,275 --> 00:14:21,110
[AUDIENCE] Yes!

253
00:14:21,193 --> 00:14:25,739
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

254
00:14:30,536 --> 00:14:32,580
So, is it true?

255
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,957
You were kidnapped as a child,

256
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:38,294
and that became the basis of
your first bestselling novel,

257
00:14:38,377 --> 00:14:42,256
which is based on you dealing
with your personal trauma,

258
00:14:42,339 --> 00:14:43,424
correct?

259
00:14:46,135 --> 00:14:48,137
That's not in the script.

260
00:14:48,804 --> 00:14:50,055
Iñigo.

261
00:14:50,139 --> 00:14:54,560
Iñigo, can we please stick
to the approved questions?

262
00:14:54,643 --> 00:14:56,228
Nod if you understand.

263
00:14:56,312 --> 00:14:57,980
Nod if you...

264
00:14:58,063 --> 00:15:05,070
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

265
00:15:10,492 --> 00:15:13,412
We didn't know these were
based on true stories.

266
00:15:13,495 --> 00:15:15,581
- [CYRUS CHUCKLES]
- So, were you kidnapped?

267
00:15:15,664 --> 00:15:16,957
Can you confirm it?

268
00:15:18,834 --> 00:15:23,714
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

269
00:15:30,095 --> 00:15:31,764
All I can say is this.

270
00:15:34,308 --> 00:15:35,392
Yes.

271
00:15:37,436 --> 00:15:38,854
There is indeed a woman.

272
00:15:42,816 --> 00:15:45,986
And she's my inspiration
for writing this book.

273
00:15:46,070 --> 00:15:48,072
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

274
00:15:48,155 --> 00:15:50,324
She's actually here
with us today.

275
00:15:51,617 --> 00:15:53,035
For real?

276
00:15:57,581 --> 00:16:04,588
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

277
00:16:07,383 --> 00:16:09,802
Kim Marie, can you take over
for a moment?

278
00:16:11,261 --> 00:16:13,681
[IÑIGO] You have to tell us
who she is.

279
00:16:14,723 --> 00:16:16,183
Give us a name,
or else none of us

280
00:16:16,266 --> 00:16:18,018
will be able to sleep tonight.

281
00:16:18,102 --> 00:16:20,062
- Hm?
- [WOMAN 1] Girlfriend reveal!

282
00:16:20,145 --> 00:16:22,272
Yes! Girlfriend reveal!

283
00:16:22,356 --> 00:16:25,818
[AUDIENCE CHANTING]
Girlfriend reveal!

284
00:16:25,901 --> 00:16:29,488
Girlfriend reveal!
Girlfriend reveal!

285
00:16:29,571 --> 00:16:31,824
- Girlfriend reveal!
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

286
00:16:31,907 --> 00:16:33,951
Don't make a scene.

287
00:16:34,034 --> 00:16:37,037
Robert, I won't let my sons
be put on the spot.

288
00:16:37,121 --> 00:16:38,706
This should stop.

289
00:16:39,248 --> 00:16:40,374
Carlota.

290
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:43,460
I'm not going
to let this happen.

291
00:16:44,211 --> 00:16:49,508
Girlfriend reveal!
Girlfriend reveal!

292
00:16:49,591 --> 00:16:52,386
- Girlfriend reveal!
- Morpheus!

293
00:16:52,469 --> 00:16:59,476
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

294
00:17:01,019 --> 00:17:02,688
- Ma'am, please!
- Ma'am, no!

295
00:17:02,771 --> 00:17:05,941
Don't stop me.
I have to talk to your host.

296
00:17:06,275 --> 00:17:09,445
Madam, just stay calm.

297
00:17:09,528 --> 00:17:11,613
Wasn't he properly briefed?

298
00:17:11,697 --> 00:17:13,824
How did his questions
get past you?

299
00:17:13,907 --> 00:17:17,327
We're looking into that, madam.
But for now, please calm down.

300
00:17:17,411 --> 00:17:19,747
Yes. Let's all take
a deep breath.

301
00:17:19,830 --> 00:17:21,540
- Yes.
- Inhale, everybody.

302
00:17:21,623 --> 00:17:23,459
- [ALL INHALE DEEPLY]
- Exhale.

303
00:17:23,542 --> 00:17:25,377
[ALL EXHALE DEEPLY]

304
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:28,839
Excuse me. Hi.

305
00:17:28,922 --> 00:17:31,091
Iñigo Castro, right?

306
00:17:32,050 --> 00:17:33,469
Do I know you?

307
00:17:33,552 --> 00:17:35,137
Uh, no.

308
00:17:35,220 --> 00:17:38,724
But I think the question
you should be asking is...

309
00:17:38,807 --> 00:17:41,894
how well do you know
the Castillos?

310
00:17:41,977 --> 00:17:45,189
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

311
00:17:45,272 --> 00:17:47,983
- Inhale.
- [ALL INHALE DEEPLY]

312
00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:50,152
- Exhale. Drop your jaw.
- [ALL EXHALE DEEPLY]

313
00:17:50,235 --> 00:17:57,242
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

314
00:18:14,843 --> 00:18:15,844
Boss.

315
00:18:18,138 --> 00:18:20,724
What are you doing here?
Just go back inside.

316
00:18:21,391 --> 00:18:24,186
Boss, there's something
I have to tell you.

317
00:18:24,269 --> 00:18:26,563
Go back inside. That's an order.

318
00:18:29,233 --> 00:18:31,318
Boss, please wait.

319
00:18:32,194 --> 00:18:33,195
[SIGHS]

320
00:18:33,612 --> 00:18:35,781
I'm not here as your secretary.

321
00:18:36,281 --> 00:18:38,617
I'm here
to explain myself to you.

322
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:40,202
You don't have
to explain anything,

323
00:18:40,285 --> 00:18:42,412
and I told you, I can handle it.

324
00:18:43,622 --> 00:18:44,832
I know.

325
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:48,669
After all these years
of working together,

326
00:18:48,752 --> 00:18:52,381
I can already tell
when you're hurt.

327
00:18:52,464 --> 00:18:54,466
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

328
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:59,596
I don't want us to part ways
with you having the wrong idea.

329
00:19:01,473 --> 00:19:04,101
I want to clarify...

330
00:19:05,644 --> 00:19:08,564
...that the reason I tried
to ignore your hints...

331
00:19:09,565 --> 00:19:11,441
...your courtship...

332
00:19:13,402 --> 00:19:15,487
...is not because of Cyrus.

333
00:19:17,072 --> 00:19:19,199
He has nothing to do with it.

334
00:19:22,619 --> 00:19:25,747
Then what are you trying to say?

335
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:35,799
I just wasn't really sure about
what I felt for you before.

336
00:19:40,178 --> 00:19:41,597
But now...

337
00:19:44,016 --> 00:19:49,354
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

338
00:19:51,690 --> 00:19:55,319
What about Ninja Boy?

339
00:19:55,611 --> 00:19:57,279
It doesn't matter.

340
00:19:59,823 --> 00:20:02,075
You're the one
I'm choosing, Brandon.

341
00:20:07,497 --> 00:20:14,504
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

342
00:20:18,258 --> 00:20:25,265
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

343
00:20:43,533 --> 00:20:50,540
["HERE WITH YOU"
BY BINI PLAYING]

344
00:21:00,008 --> 00:21:06,223
["HERE WITH YOU" CONTINUES]

345
00:21:21,279 --> 00:21:27,327
["HERE WITH YOU" CONTINUES]

346
00:21:46,138 --> 00:21:53,145
["HERE WITH YOU" CONTINUES]

347
00:22:05,490 --> 00:22:12,456
["HERE WITH YOU" CONTINUES]

348
00:22:28,972 --> 00:22:31,808
I was forced to ask
those questions by a reporter.

349
00:22:31,892 --> 00:22:33,894
- Who?
- Troy Sebastian.

350
00:22:33,977 --> 00:22:35,979
Troy, you were just supposed
to help me find

351
00:22:36,063 --> 00:22:38,899
the kid I was kidnapped with,
so what happened?

352
00:22:38,982 --> 00:22:41,860
Tell me the truth.
Why are you doing this?

353
00:22:41,943 --> 00:22:44,237
- Is it for your career?
- [CLICKS TONGUE]

354
00:22:44,321 --> 00:22:45,322
Troy!

355
00:22:45,405 --> 00:22:47,657
I need to talk to Sir Robert.

356
00:22:47,741 --> 00:22:49,076
I want to apologize.

357
00:22:49,159 --> 00:22:53,246
The only time we're going to
talk to my parents together...

358
00:22:54,164 --> 00:22:56,583
is when I introduce you
to them as my girlfriend.

359
00:22:58,835 --> 00:23:00,712
Kimberly Liwanag...

360
00:23:02,255 --> 00:23:05,384
will you give me the privilege
of being my girlfriend?

361
00:23:07,094 --> 00:23:08,220
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]
